title: Did Ukraine Kill Russia’s Black Sea Fleet Commander in a Missile Strike?
description: Moscow released video on Tuesday purporting to show that its Black Sea fleet commander is still alive, despite Ukraine’s claim that he was killed in a major missile strike.

title: In Russia-Ukraine War, Disinformation Is a Weapon Regularly Deployed
description: It is often hard to know when battlefield reports are false or why they may have been disseminated.

title: Wednesday Briefing: South China Sea Tensions Cross a Line
description: Plus presidential portraits, this time for Africa.

title: Canadian Parliamentary Leader Quits After Honoring Ukrainian Who Fought for Nazis
description: Anthony Rota, the speaker of Canada’s House of Commons, introduced a 98-year-old veteran of an SS unit as a ‘hero’ in front of Ukraine’s president.

title: Erdogan Says Turkey’s Parliament Will Ratify Sweden’s Entry into NATO if the U.S. Sells Turkey Fighter Jets
description: A bid to join the military alliance has been held up for months by the Turkish leader.

title: Peter Nygard, Disgraced Fashion Designer, Faces Trial in Toronto
description: Mr. Nygard, the 82-year-old former executive behind a defunct women’s clothing company, is accused of sexual assault and forcible confinement.

title: Russia-Ukraine War: Russia Seeks to Show Commander Is Alive After Ukraine Claimed His Killing
description: A day after Ukraine claimed to have killed the commander of Russia’s Black Sea Fleet, Russian state media broadcast footage of the admiral, Viktor Sokolov, in a meeting of defense officials.

title: The Philippines’ Tension With China Crosses New Line in South China Sea
description: The Philippines is pushing back against China’s territorial claims. But Chinese forces have been unrelenting in using direct confrontation, raising worries about an escalation.

title: The U.S. Is Sending Depleted Uranium Munitions to Ukraine. What Does That Mean?
description: The material is denser than steel, and shells made from it can penetrate enemy tanks’ armor. But they leave behind radioactive dust that can be harmful.

title: Ukraine-Russia War Shows Fight for Democracy Continues
description: The war between Russia and Ukraine may be an extreme example of the fight over which form of government works best for its citizens, but there are others.

title: Liberal Democracy in the World View
description: The belief that individual rights are “self-evident” is being challenged, with large parts of the world instead prioritizing collective benefits.

title: Behind China-U.S. Tensions Are Misunderstandings, Author Says.
description: In an interview, the economist Keyu Jin says much of the world is asking the wrong questions — and so is drawing outdated conclusions.

title: What to Know About 5 People Suspected of Spying for Russia in the U.K.
description: Three men and two women, all citizens of Bulgaria, will appear in court on Tuesday after being charged with conspiracy to conduct espionage.

title: Nagorno-Karabakh Fuel Depot Blast Kills at Least 20
description: The cause of the Monday blast in the breakaway region of Azerbaijan, where thousands have been fleeing for Armenia, was still unclear. Hundreds were wounded.

title: Tuesday Briefing
description: A blow to the Russian military.

title: In a Port City Severed From the Sea, Young Sailors Feel Adrift
description: With Russia trying to maintain military control of the Black Sea, Odesa is disconnected from its waters — and its history.

title: After Taking Away Enemies’ Citizenship, Nicaragua Takes Their Homes
description: Nicaragua’s government has begun confiscating the homes of former political prisoners and dissidents forced into exile, just as the country did in the 1980s.
